  // ── STOICISM ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  {'id': 'st001', 'text': 'You have power over your mind — not outside events. Realize this, and you will find strength.', 'author': 'Marcus Aurelius', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st002', 'text': 'The obstacle is the way.', 'author': 'Marcus Aurelius', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st003', 'text': 'Waste no more time arguing about what a good man should be. Be one.', 'author': 'Marcus Aurelius', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st004', 'text': 'He who fears death will never do anything worthy of a man who is alive.', 'author': 'Seneca', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st005', 'text': 'Luck is what happens when preparation meets opportunity.', 'author': 'Seneca', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st006', 'text': 'It is not the man who has too little, but the man who craves more, that is poor.', 'author': 'Seneca', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st007', 'text': 'Make the best use of what is in your power, and take the rest as it happens.', 'author': 'Epictetus', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st008', 'text': 'He is a wise man who does not grieve for the things which he has not, but rejoices for those which he has.', 'author': 'Epictetus', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st009', 'text': 'The happiness of your life depends upon the quality of your thoughts.', 'author': 'Marcus Aurelius', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st010', 'text': 'Very little is needed to make a happy life; it is all within yourself, in your way of thinking.', 'author': 'Marcus Aurelius', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st011', 'text': 'If it is not right, do not do it; if it is not true, do not say it.', 'author': 'Marcus Aurelius', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st012', 'text': 'Do not indulge in dreams of having what you have not, but reckon up the chief of the blessings you do possess.', 'author': 'Epictetus', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st013', 'text': 'What we cannot control is not ours.', 'author': 'Epictetus', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st014', 'text': 'Begin at once to live, and count each separate day as a separate life.', 'author': 'Seneca', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st015', 'text': 'We suffer more often in imagination than in reality.', 'author': 'Seneca', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st016', 'text': 'No man is free who is not master of himself.', 'author': 'Epictetus', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st017', 'text': 'The soul that moves in the world of the senses and yet keeps the senses in harmony... finds rest in quietness.', 'author': 'Marcus Aurelius', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st018', 'text': 'How does it help to make troubles heavier by bemoaning them?', 'author': 'Seneca', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st019', 'text': 'He who is brave is free.', 'author': 'Seneca', 'category': 'stoicism'},
  {'id': 'st020', 'text': 'Man is not worried by real problems so much as by his imagined anxieties about real problems.', 'author': 'Epictetus', 'category': 'stoicism'},
